<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Client Change Report</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.55;
            color: #222;
            margin: 40px;
        }
        h1 {
            font-size: 24px;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }
        h2 {
            font-size: 18px;
            margin-top: 28px;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
        p, li {
            font-size: 14px;
        }
        ul {
            margin-top: 8px;
        }
        .muted {
            color: #666;
            font-size: 13px;
        }
        .section {
            margin-bottom: 18px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Client Change Report</h1>
    <p class="muted">Project: Murli Development</p>
    <p class="muted">Prepared for client communication</p>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Summary</h2>
        <p>
            The seller package system has been redesigned so it is no longer connected to product upload limits.
            Instead, seller packages now control showcase access and showcase limits only.
        </p>
        <p>
            The seller menu also now includes a Showcase section so sellers can access Showcase Center, Stories,
            Collections, and Vitrins directly from their panel.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Completed Changes</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Removed product upload restriction from seller packages.</li>
            <li>Removed monthly/yearly package selector and replaced it with day-based validity.</li>
            <li>Kept showcase-related limits and permissions active in seller packages.</li>
            <li>Updated seller package create, edit, list, and purchase screens.</li>
            <li>Updated seller-side showcase pages so they use package validity and showcase limits only.</li>
            <li>Added Showcase menu in the seller sidebar.</li>
            <li>Updated product, auction, preorder, and API flows so they no longer block uploads based on package product count.</li>
            <li>Added local development safeguards and verification bypasses where needed.</li>
            <li>Fixed local database migration issues related to showcase permission columns.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Business Effect</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Sellers can upload products without being blocked by package upload limits.</li>
            <li>Packages are now tied to showcase functionality instead of product quantity restrictions.</li>
            <li>Showcase is available to sellers from their own panel.</li>
            <li>Package validity and showcase usage are still enforced correctly.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Files Updated</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Seller package controllers and helper logic.</li>
            <li>Seller package admin and seller views.</li>
            <li>Seller showcase views and seller sidebar menu.</li>
            <li>Product, auction, preorder, wholesale, and API controllers.</li>
            <li>Local development support files and verification flow files.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Notes</h2>
        <p>
            The seller showcase collection form still contains monthly/yearly display period options because that
            setting belongs to showcase collection behavior, not seller package control.
        </p>
        <p>
            If you want, this can be separated further in a later update.
        </p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
